# App Installer Version Information

## Current Versions

**GUI Version:** 2.0.0
**CLI Version:** 2.0.0
**Release Date:** 2025-12-16

## Version History

### 2.0.0 (GUI & CLI) - 2025-12-16 - MAJOR CROSS-PLATFORM RELEASE
- **BREAKING CHANGE:** Full cross-platform refactoring for Windows, macOS, and Linux
- **NEW:** Created AppInstallerCore.psm1 shared module (373 lines)
- **NEW:** Cross-platform path handling (Windows: %USERPROFILE%, macOS/Linux: ~/.mytech-today)
- **NEW:** Platform detection with graceful degradation for GUI on non-Windows platforms
- **NEW:** Dynamic application registry loading from apps-manifest.json
- **NEW:** Support for multiple package managers (winget, brew, apt, dnf, pacman, snap)
- **IMPROVED:** Eliminated ~600 lines of code duplication
- **IMPROVED:** Single source of truth for application definitions
- **IMPROVED:** Comprehensive testing guidance for all platforms
- **GUI:** Now detects platform early and offers CLI fallback on macOS/Linux
- **GUI:** Added -ForceCLI parameter for testing
- **CLI:** Full cross-platform support with automatic package manager detection
- **CLI:** Platform-aware application filtering
- See REFACTORING-SUMMARY.md for complete details

### 1.5.0 (GUI) / 1.6.0 (CLI) - 2025-12-15
- Added automatic Start Menu shortcut creation for Chrome Remote Desktop
- Fixed Chrome Remote Desktop winget package ID
- Enhanced error handling with comprehensive winget error code mapping
- Improved terminal compatibility with ASCII text markers

### 1.4.5 (GUI) - 2025-11-11
- Multi-line button text with narrower width
- Improved button layout and spacing

### 1.4.4 (GUI) / 1.5.4 (CLI) - 2025-11-11
- Fixed GitHub URLs for scripts repository
- Enabled online loading of responsive and logging modules

### 1.4.1 (GUI) / 1.5.3 (CLI) - 2025-11-11
- Added uninstall applications feature
- Confirmation dialogs and progress tracking

## Semantic Versioning

This project follows [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/):
- **MAJOR** version for incompatible API changes
- **MINOR** version for new functionality in a backwards compatible manner
- **PATCH** version for backwards compatible bug fixes

